cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on keyphrase generation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses Seq2Seq models and attention mechanisms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with generating relevant keyphrases from source text. It also involves techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) such as beam search and attention mechanisms. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for keyphrase generation.
